This paper deals with energy efficiency and delay quality of service in wireless networks, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). The paper uses game theory to model the behavior of users in a wireless network, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under game theory (cs.GT). The paper also considers the utility function, which measures the number of reliable bits transmitted per Joule of energy consumed, indicating the possibility of the paper being categorized under information theory (cs.IT). The paper also considers the delay quality of service, which suggests the possibility of the paper being categorized under control systems (cs.SY). Finally, the paper quantifies the tradeoffs among throughput, delay, network capacity, and energy efficiency, indicating the possibility of the paper being categorized under multimedia (cs.MM).
